## Year One Training Program — Honest Assessment

**What was delivered:**
- Annual HIPAA and security awareness training module: completed by 100% of staff
- Contingency plan training (CP-3): completed by all designated staff members
- Access control training: delivered as part of IS-AC-001 policy acknowledgment process at account provisioning

**What was demonstrated:**
- Completion rates: 100% (KPI-AT-1 — Green)
- CP-3 retention: approximately 50% — one of two staff members tested informally could not describe the paper-based downtime procedure (Day 79 self-assessment finding)
- Phishing recognition: not measured — phishing simulation program not implemented

**What was not demonstrated:**
- Whether staff can identify a targeted phishing email under realistic conditions
- Whether staff understand the specific escalation steps for a security incident (beyond module completion)
- Whether staff who completed the HIPAA training understand their personal obligation to report observed privacy violations

The honest year-one assessment: the training program meets minimum compliance requirements and has produced documented completion. It has not produced demonstrated behavioral effectiveness for the two most important behavioral outcomes in the current threat environment — phishing recognition and incident escalation.

