## Training Effectiveness Measurement Framework

| Metric | Type | Measurement Method | Target |
|---|---|---|---|
| AT-2 completion rate | KPI | Training platform completion records | 100% annually |
| CP-3 retention rate | Effectiveness | Quarterly informal retention check (2-3 staff per quarter) | 100% can describe downtime procedure |
| Phishing simulation click rate | KRI | Quarterly GoPhish results | Below 10% by Q4 |
| Phishing simulation reporting rate | Effectiveness | Quarterly GoPhish results | Above 30% reporting by Q4 |
| CM-3 compliance rate (IT Admin) | Effectiveness | Monitoring log: changes preceded by ISSO notification | 100% |
| Incident escalation accuracy | Effectiveness | IR-3 tabletop results | All participants can describe escalation steps |

The critical design choice in this framework is including both KPIs (implementation metrics — did training happen?) and effectiveness metrics (did training change behavior?). Year one had only KPIs. Year two adds the effectiveness metrics that tell the ISSO whether the training is actually working.

